Package core

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Equation
    Class that represents an equation An equation is constructed from two terms of equal sort
    EquationSystem
    Class that represents an instance of the inductive theorem, which consists of a set equations over a signature Sigma, a subset of Sigma called C (constructors) and an equation that should be proven
    Function
    Class that represents a function A function has a name, 0 or more input sorts, and one output sort
    FunctionTerm
    Class that represents a term constructed by applying a function to zero or more arguments
    Prover
    Class with static functions that can prove an EquationSystem
    RewriteThread  
    Sort
    Class that represents a sort.
    Term
    Abstract class that represents a term
    Variable
    Class that represents a variable A variable is a Term and additionally has a name
